reviewText: "Know thy self" was never meant to be taken in the literal sense. The sound track by Ronit Kirchman is beautiful. And the short encounter with artist, Rande Cook, was almost worth it. But for those seeking something beyond voyeurism, think again.

This documentary is equally fascinating, troubling and erotic as it takes us on the journey of Brody Fox, from the depths of substance abuse despair to the transformative power of art, love and the flesh. I didn't expect to be riveted, but I was. Bravo! from Donovan
